    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "-1 for moving dashboards, we would lose the ability to atomically rename metrics in a single commit and update the dashboard when adding new metrics in a single MR. \r\n\r\nIf we remove dashboards this would also warrant to move the docs to a separate repository which is also not a decoupling I would be in favor of.\r\n\r\nTo reduce noise for something like release notes could think of a concept similar to [conventional commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/) to better categorize commits, things like refactoring code, docs, dashboard updates, CI/CD updates, etc. should not show up in the release notes.",
